{"id":"meekness","term":"Meekness","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>A calm temper of mind, not easily provoked (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"James 3:13\">James 3:13</a>). Peculiar promises are made to the meek (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Matthew 5:5\">Matt. 5:5</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Isaiah 66:2\">Isa. 66:2</a>). The cultivation of this spirit is enjoined (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Colossians 3:12\">Col. 3:12</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Timothy 6:11\">1 Tim. 6:11</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Zephaniah 2:3\">Zeph. 2:3</a>), and is exemplified in Christ (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Matthew 11:29\">Matt. 11:29</a>), Abraham (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 13:1\">Gen. 13</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 16:5\">16:5</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 16:6\">6</a>) Moses (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Numbers 12:3\">Num. 12:3</a>), David (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Zechariah 12:8\">Zech. 12:8</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"2 Samuel 16:10\">2 Sam. 16:10</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"2 Samuel 16:12\">12</a>), and Paul (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Corinthians 9:19\">1 Cor. 9:19</a>).</p>\n\u0000","refs":["James 3:13","Matthew 5:5","Isaiah 66:2","Colossians 3:12","1 Timothy 6:11","Zephaniah 2:3","Matthew 11:29","Genesis 13:1","Genesis 16:5","Genesis 16:6","Numbers 12:3","Zechariah 12:8","2 Samuel 16:10","2 Samuel 16:12","1 Corinthians 9:19"]}